.TH "ima_get_kexec_buffer" 9 "ima_get_kexec_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ima_get_kexec_buffer \- get IMA buffer from the previous kernel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ima_get_kexec_buffer
.BI "(void **addr "  ","
.BI "size_t *size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
On successful return, set to point to the buffer contents.
.IP "size" 12
On successful return, set to the buffer size.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno on error.
